biography:
Progress was a group of Club DJ's who had a massive hit with "Everybody" featuring the artist Boy Wunda (1999). The DJ's were Julian Foddy, Pete Wye and Russell Davison.
Russel Davison was the promoter for "Progress" nights in Derby at the Eclipse club in the mid to late 90's which featured Julian and Pete.
name: Progress

theaudiodb.biography_en:
Progress was a group of Club DJ's who had a massive hit with "Everybody" featuring the artist Boy Wunda (1999). The DJ's were Julian Foddy, Pete Wye and Russell Davison.
Russel Davison was the promoter for "Progress" nights in Derby at the Eclipse club in the mid to late 90's which featured Julian and Pete.

lastfm.bio_content: 1. Progress is a band from Heerlen (Mijnstreek Oost. Netherlands). the band is still going strong in 2008 and finally presents their long awaited debut mcd 'the crosses we bear'. Progress quit in 2009. After playing a reunion show in 2010 or 2011 some members decided they wanted to give it another shot. Recordings of a new 4 song EP have just been finished. It's not decided when it's going to be released yet. But one thing's for sure, PROGRESS is ready to play a lot of shows in 2013. 2. Progress is a hip-hop duo that consists of Infinito 2017 and SavSola. Their released their debut EP titled Advanced Copy: Breaking Your Dreams EP on February 15, 2011, via Joe Left Hand Records. 3. Progress is a hardcore band from Connecticut that is signed to Detonate Records. 4. A progressive rock band from Tallinn, Estonia. 5. Early/Mid 80s punk band from Yugoslavia 6. Progress is a Christian alternative band formed in Boksburg, South Africa in 2011. The band consists of Kyla Boshoff and Megan Olyott as core members both playing guitar and singing. The band recorded one known song 'Won't Stop' before a falling out between band members caused the band to break up. 7. Progress Chukwuyem from Ika South, Delta State, was the seventh Nigerian Idol in May 2022. A gospel singer, the first single was " Lift Me Up" released 2022-07-01. Read more on Last.fm.
